<%# Cerberus override of Blacklight's catalog/_search_sidebar.

    Renders the facet sidebar (the gem's sidebar_component, "Limit your search")
    and, beneath it, the results-display controls — Sort / Per-page / View-type —
    relocated here from the top of the results column so the result list can rise
    level with the sidebar. Styled as a full-width vertical stack separated from
    the facets by a hairline rule in app/assets/stylesheets/_search_controls.scss
    (no visible label — the controls are self-evident; the section's aria-label
    carries the accessible name).

    Controls only render when there are results to act on; an empty container
    suppresses the whole sidebar upstream (communities/collections show), so we
    never get here with an empty response in that case. %>
<% conf = blacklight_config.view_config(document_index_view_type) %>
<%= render conf.sidebar_component.new(blacklight_config: blacklight_config,
                                      response: @response,
                                      view_config: conf) %>

<% if @response && @response.total_count.to_i.positive? %>
  <section class="sidebar-display-controls" aria-label="<%= t('blacklight.search.per_page.aria_label') %>">
    <%= render_results_collection_tools wrapping_class: "search-widgets" %>
  </section>
<% end %>
